<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 1:23PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern
Pushmataha and southwestern Pittsburg Counties through 215 PM CDT...
At 123 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles east of Scipio to 3 miles east of Haywood
to 2 miles north of Wardville. Movement was southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Alderson...
Haywood...                        Mcalester Regional Airport...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Dow...
Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
